Citations
Date:  0/0/1949
Source:  High Country Days
Author:  NEWTON
Vol / Page:  54
Edition:
Quote:  The wool rollers and fleece pickers who were paid by the week spent the smoko spell resting. Some of the more energetic tried their hand at shearing, a practice known as `barrowing'. Usually these sheep went to the learner['s tally] or to any of the older or slower shearers.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1989
Source:  NZ English Newsletter
Author:
Vol / Page:  3/21
Edition:
Quote:  <i>barrowing:</i> A term to describe the action of a shed hand who finishes off a sheep for a shearer after the bell has gone for the end of a run.
Notes:  (Wallace Shearing Glossary)
